Fundamental Astrophysical Questions:
  Origins of the Universe: Investigate the theoretical foundations of the universe's creation and evlution.
  Nature of Dark Matter and Dark Energy: Contribute to the understanding of these enigmatic cosmic components.
  Exoplanet Habitability: Explore conditions conductive to life on planets beyond our solar system.

Methodological Advancements:
  Data-Intensive Approaches: Implement machine learning algorithms for efficient data processing and analysis.
  Multi-Wavelength observations: Combine data from various wavelengths to gain comprehensive insights into celestial phenomena.
  Interdisciplinary Collaborations: Foster collaborations with experts in related fields, such as physics, computer science, and engineering.

